          <!-- Conclusion -->
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">The Bottom Line on Concrete Quality</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              Good concrete isn't expensive - bad concrete is. The difference between 20 MPa and 32 MPa is about 
              $50 per cubic meter. The cost to remove and replace failed concrete starts at $500 per cubic meter. 
              In 39 years, we've never had a client regret ordering better concrete, but we've demolished plenty 
              of cheap concrete that didn't make it through two winters.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              Toronto's freeze-thaw cycles are brutal. Salt exposure is constant. Our clay soils move. If you're 
              not using air-entrained, low W/C concrete for exterior work, you're building in failure. Follow the 
              specifications, test everything, and never let anyone add water on site.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              At Toronto Concrete, we don't compromise on materials. Every mix is designed for its specific application 
              and exposure conditions. We test, we document, and we stand behind our work with a 25-year warranty. 
              Because concrete done right lasts generations - concrete done wrong doesn't last a decade.
            </p>
